## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="0442c-102">Eine Instanz von <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> wird erstellt, wenn die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> oder <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> -Objekt löst ein `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` Ereignis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-102">An instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> is created when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> object raises an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0442c-103">Zum Abrufen von Informationen im Zusammenhang mit einem `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` Ereignis, Zugriff auf die folgenden Eigenschaften im Handler für das Ereignis:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-103">To obtain information related to an `AudioSignalProblemOccurred` event, access the following properties in the handler for the event:</span></span>  

-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A>  

-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A>  

-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A>  

-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A>  

 <span data-ttu-id="0442c-104">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> -Eigenschaft verweist auf das Eingabegerät Position in der generierten Audiostream.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-104">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioPosition%2A> property references the input device's position in its generated audio stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0442c-105">Im Gegensatz dazu, die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> Eigenschaft verweist auf die Erkennung Position innerhalb der Audioeingabe.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-105">By contrast, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.RecognizerAudioPosition%2A> property references the recognizer's position within its audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0442c-106">Diese Positionen können unterschiedlich sein.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-106">These positions can be different.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="0442c-107">Weitere Informationen finden Sie unter [mit Spracherkennung Recognition Ereignissen](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-107">For more information, see [Using Speech Recognition Events](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="0442c-108">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> Eigenschaft angibt, welches Problem aufgetreten ist.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-108">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs.AudioSignalProblem%2A> property indicates which problem occurred.</span></span>  

 <span data-ttu-id="0442c-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> wird von <xref:System.EventArgs> abgeleitet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-109"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  



## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="0442c-110">Das folgende Beispiel definiert einen Ereignishandler, die sammelt Informationen über ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> Ereignis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="0442c-110">The following example defines an event handler that gathers information about an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioSignalProblemOccurred> event.</span></span>  

```csharp  

private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  

// Initialize the speech recognition engine.  
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  

  // Add a handler for the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event.  
  sre.AudioSignalProblemOccurred += new EventHandler<AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs>(sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred);  
}  

// Gather information when the AudioSignalProblemOccurred event is raised.  
void sre_AudioSignalProblemOccurred(object sender, AudioSignalProblemOccurredEventArgs e)  
{  
  StringBuilder details = new StringBuilder();  

  details.AppendLine("Audio signal problem information:");  
  details.AppendFormat(  
    " Audio level:               {0}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio position:            {1}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Audio signal problem:      {2}" + Environment.NewLine +  
    " Recognition engine audio position: {3}" + Environment.NewLine,  
    e.AudioLevel, e.AudioPosition,  e.AudioSignalProblem,  
    e.RecognizerAudioPosition);  

  // Insert additional event handler code here.  
}  

```
